            <p>
                MyDoggy is a Java docking framework for use in cross-platform Swing applications.
                MyDoggy is an IntelliJ Idea like docking framework for managing secondary windows within the main
                window. MyDoggy allows to move, resize or extract those secondary windows.
                Also, MyDoggy provides support for content management of the main window.
            </p>

            <subsection name="Main Modules">
                <p>
                    MyDoggy is separated in two main modules.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <a href="./mydoggy-api/index.html">MyDoggy-Api</a>
                        contains the application program interface of MyDoggy to manage every aspects of
                        the framework.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a href="./mydoggy-plaf/index.html">MyDoggy-Plaf</a>
                        contains the default implementation of mydoggy-api.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </subsection>

            <subsection name="Other Modules">
                There are also other modules that cover secondary aspects of MyDoggy.
